description: These are the photon ID, Pixel veto and CSEV Scale Factors (nominal, up or down) for 2018 Ultra Legacy dataset. Each kind of scale factors, depend on the chosen working point, some other quantities. More information is below! Please keep in the mind that if your analysis is sensitive to high pT photons (>500 GeV), please refer https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMS/EGMPhotonIDHighPtPhotons

corrections.name: UL-Photon-ID-SF
corrections.description: These are the photon ID Scale Factors (nominal, up or down) for 2018 Ultra Legacy dataset. They are available for the cut-based and MVA IDs. They are dependent on the transverse momenta and pseudorapidity of the photon.

inputs.name: ValType
inputs.description: sf/sfup/sfdown (sfup = sf + syst, sfdown = sf - syst)

inputs.name: WorkingPoint
inputs.description: Working Point of choice : Loose, Medium etc.

output.name: weight
output.description: value of scale factor (nominal, up or down)

corrections.name: UL-Photon-PixVeto-SF
corrections.description: These are the Photon Pixel Veto Scale Factors (nominal, up or down) for 2018 Ultra Legacy dataset. They are available for the cut-based and MVA IDs. For each working point of choice, they are dependent on the photon pseudorapidity and R9: Possible bin choices: ['EBInc','EBHighR9','EBLowR9','EEInc','EEHighR9','EELowR9']

inputs.name: ValType
inputs.description: sf/sfup/sfdown (sfup = sf + syst, sfdown = sf - syst)

inputs.name: WorkingPoint
inputs.description: Working Point of choice : Loose, Medium etc.

output.name: weight
output.description: value of scale factor (nominal, up or down)
